CardNames.1:
Witnesses

Q: Do you have to control Witnesses to Catapult move them?
A: Yes!

Q: When I move Loyal ships, can I move a Witness along with them even if I am not taking a Catapult move?
A: Yes.
CardNames.4:
Psionic Liaisons

Q: Can I use Dealmakers or other sources of extra influence to gain more Psionic?
A: No. This card can only be triggered once, for spending the action pip from Copy to influence.
CardNames.8:
Empathy for All

Q: How does the harm rule work with battle?
A: Resolve it after dealing hits but before resolving raids. Always do this, even if no hits are dealt!

Q: How does the harm rule work with battle?

CardNames.10:
Reconcile with the Outraged

Q: How does this interact with Psionic Monopoly?
A: The consent of the Monopoly holder is still required to give Psionic. As noted on Monopoly Consent, consent can be forced by returning their Favor in the Call to Order.
CardNames.11:
Rebuke of the Empaths

Q: What happens when there are not enough Psionic in the supply?
A: The player with initiative chooses who gains Psionic.
